msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/date"
msgid "10th of February, 1943 · Krasny Bor, Leningrad Oblast"
msgstr "10 de febrero, 1942 - Krasny Bor, Leningrado."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/name"
msgid "The Legend of Krasny Bor"
msgstr "La leyenda de Krasny Bor"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/name_big"
msgid "The Legend of Krasny Bor"
msgstr "La leyenda de Krasny Bor"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/hint/01"
msgid "The \"Blue Division\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/01"
msgid "Soldiers of the 250th Infantry Division! Listen up!"
msgstr "Soldados de la 250 division de infantería! Atención!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/02"
msgid ""
"The Soviet counteroffensive is at large! The bolsheviks are eager to break "
"the Leningrad encirclement and are dashing toward your defences with armour! "
"Everything is at stake!"
msgstr ""
"Los soviéticos han comenzado su avalancha de hierro! Los bolcheviques "
"piensan romper el cerco de leningrado, y avanzan hacia aquí con blindados. "
"Todo está en juego!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/03"
msgid ""
"Today is the day where the Red wave will meet the Blue wall! You already "
"defeated the communists once. I am confident you will do it once more! "
msgstr ""
"Hoy es el día en el que la marea roja será detenida por la barrera Azul! Ya "
"habeis derrotado al comunismo una vez! Espero que repitan esa hazaña!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/04"
msgid ""
"Your objective is to hold our rear headquarters at all costs, but it will "
"also be convenient to secure our secondary key objectives: "
msgstr ""
"Su objetivo es defender este cuartel a toda costa, pero Tambien será "
"conveniente mantener bajo control los objeticos secundarios:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/04a"
msgid "The railway station,..."
msgstr "La estación de ferrocarril…"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/04b"
msgid "...the artillery battery,..."
msgstr "...La artillería..."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/04c"
msgid ""
"...and the communications vehicle, which you need to keep operational to "
"maintain radio-contact to call for reinforcements. "
msgstr ""
"...Y el vehículo de radiocomunicaciones, el cual se debe mantener "
"operacional para poder llamar a los refuerzos."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/05"
msgid ""
"I regret to inform you our Anti-tank weaponry is in extremely short supply. "
"However, we have reserves of mines and grenades to deal with the enemy "
"tanks. "
msgstr ""
"Siento tener que comunicarles que temenos muy poco arsenal de cañones anti-"
"tanque. Afortunadamente, sí que temenos reservas de minas y granadas, para "
"poder combatir los blindados enemigos."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/06"
msgid ""
"The enemy has commenced to bombard our first line. Get to work laying mine-"
"fields and prepare for the enemy assault.  "
msgstr ""
"El enemigo ha comenzado a bombardear nuestra primera línea. Pónganse a "
"trabajar, construyan campos de minas y prepárense para recibir a los "
"bolcheviques!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/07"
msgid ""
"The enemy is approaching. You can tell where they are coming from, as they "
"will use flares to light up the path for their tanks! Hold out until "
"sunrise. No step back!"
msgstr ""
"El enemigo está al llegar. Utilizan bengalas para poder ver hacia donde van. "
"Las bengalas les dirán desde dónde viene el enemigo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/08"
msgid ""
"Our field hospital is endangered so close to the front line. I have ordered "
"its immediate re-location. You must protect it at all costs!"
msgstr ""
"Nuestro hospital de campaña está demasiado cerca de la línea del frente. He "
"ordenado su evacuación de inmediato. Debe escoltar los camiones hasta el fin "
"de su recorrido."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/09"
msgid ""
"You should consider pulling back your forces into a second defensive line in "
"the village. It has been fortified for the occasion."
msgstr ""
"Debería plantearse consolidar la defensa en torno a la segunda línea en el "
"pueblo. Se ha fortificado para la occasion."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/comms1"
msgid ""
"The communications vehicle has been jeopardised! Try to get it back in "
"action!"
msgstr ""
"El camion de radiocomunicaciones no está operativo. Intente hacerlo "
"funcionar de nuevo para volver a tener refuerzos disponibles!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/comms2"
msgid "Reinforcements are now at your disposal."
msgstr "Los refuerzos están a su disposición."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/end"
msgid "Good job soldiers. You have once again made the Fatherland proud!"
msgstr "Buen trabajo, soldados. Vuestro país estará orgulloso de vosotros."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/hospital_complete"
msgid ""
"The evacuation of the hospital was a success. Our wounded will live to fight "
"once more."
msgstr ""
"La evacuación del hospital ha sido un éxito. Nuestros heridos volverán a "
"luchar otro día."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/hospital_fail"
msgid ""
"The trucks with the wounded have been hit! This careless escorting will not "
"be tolerated!"
msgstr "Los camiones de los heridos han sido abatidos! Esto es intolerable! "

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/hq"
msgid ""
"Enemy tanks are approaching our headquarters. See to it! They need to be "
"destroyed immediately!"
msgstr ""
"Los tanques enemigos están acercándose al cuartél general! No puede ser! "
"Destrúyanlos de inmediato!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/positions"
msgid "The soviet forces are building defensive positions!"
msgstr "Los soviéticos están construyendo posiciones defensivas!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/prisoners"
msgid ""
"The enemy has a column of prisoners being taken away. I need you to ambush "
"the column and liberate our men!"
msgstr ""
"Una columna de nuestros compatriotas prisioneros están siendo evacuados. "
"Necesito que les tienda una emboscada y libere a nuestros hombres!"

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/prisoners_complete"
msgid "Good to have our soldiers fighting for the fatherland once again!"
msgstr "Muy bien. Nuestros soldados pueden luchar por la patria una vez más!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/narrator/officer/rocket"
msgid ""
"Enemy rocket artillery in the area! Stalin's organs have arrived to set the "
"tunes for the sunrise!"
msgstr ""
"Lanzacohetes enemigos han sido avistados por aquí! Vaya, parece que los "
"órganos de Stalin van a marcar la melodía del amanecer..."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"Because the blue division held the line at Krasny Bor, the 18th army was not "
"surrounded like the 6th at Stalingrad. But they paid a terrible price; only "
"1 in five got out alive. \n"
"The Germans thought the blue division’s tenacity was unmatched. This seems "
"no more than fair, considering how little they had to defend themselves "
"against the huge odds."
msgstr ""
"Al defender Krasny Bor, la división Azul evitó que el 18 ejército no fuera "
"rodeado como ocurrió en Estalingrado. Pero pagaron un precio terrible: Solo "
"un soldado español de cada cinco consiguió sobrevivir. Consiguieron detener "
"una fuerza mucho mayor con muchos menos recursos. Los alemanes consideraron "
"que el valentía de la división Azul debió de ser el estándar para el resto "
"de la campaña del norte. Debido a las bajas, los supervivientes de la "
"división Azul fueron enviados de vuelta a España, donde nunca se les dió el "
"homenaje que se merecían. Hoy, las batallas de la división Azul, como la de "
"Krasny Bor, permanecen tabús en la sociedad moderna Española."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"Your failure to hold Krasny Bor has grave consequences; the 18th army has "
"just been cut off from the front, facing the same fate as the 6th army at "
"Stalingrad. Thousands will succumb to injury, illness and starvation. Those "
"that can still walk will be sent to Siberia. This is a dent in your "
"reputation to say the least!  \n"
msgstr "Ha fallado la misión!\n"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/place"
msgid "250th Infantry Division \"Blue Division\""
msgstr "250 division de infanteria, la División Azul"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/apminer"
msgid "AP miners"
msgstr "Mineros Anti-persona"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/artillerymen"
msgid "Artillerymen"
msgstr "Artilleros"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/atminer"
msgid "AT miners"
msgstr "Mineros Anti-tanque"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/atsquad"
msgid "AT detachment"
msgstr "Unidad Anti-tanque"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/engineer"
msgid "Field Engineers"
msgstr "Ingenieros"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/medic"
msgid "Medics"
msgstr "Sanitarios"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/mgun"
msgid "MG-42 lafette"
msgstr "MG-42 en trípode"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/squad"
msgid "Regular infantry squad"
msgstr "Escuadrón de Infantería"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/reinf/supply"
msgid "Supply crate"
msgstr "Baúl de abastecimiento"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/skip"
msgid "Skip preparation phase"
msgstr "Saltar fase de preparación"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/story"
msgid "February 1943; the Red army goes offensive in the Leningrad region. Operation \"polar star\" aims to encircle the German 18th army. One of its goals is to take Tosno, following the road and railroad, both leading straight through Krasny Bor.\n\nKrasny Bor is at the centre of attention in this mission. The initial attack is met by the Spanish Blue Division, who have dug in a handful of AT guns and a few artillery pieces at the village. With enemies approaching from all sides, this battle will be a serious test of your improvisation skills.\n\nHold your position until it is time to counterattack!"
msgstr "Febrero de 1943. El ejército Rojo comienza la ofeensiva en la región de Leningrado. La operación \"Estrella polar\"\ intent rodear al 18 ejército. Uno de sus objetivos es tomar Tosno, y deben pasar por Krasny Bor.\n\nAllí les espera la división Azul Española, donde se han atrincherado con los pocos recursos disponibles.\n\nLa batalla decisiva del cerco de Leningrado está a punto de comenzar."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/task_hospital"
msgid ""
"Escort the trucks evacuating the hospital. At least 2 trucks must survive."
msgstr ""
"Escolte a los camiones que evacúan el hospital. Al menos dos deben poder "
"escaper."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/task_main"
msgid "Don't let the enemy tanks overrun the headquarters."
msgstr "No permita a los tanques soviéticos acercarse al cuartel general."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/taskopt_arty"
msgid "Don't let the enemy tanks overrun the artillery battery"
msgstr ""
"No permita que los tanques soviéticos alcanzen la batería de artillería."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/taskopt_comms"
msgid "Keep the radio vehicle crewed and operational for reinforcements."
msgstr "Mantenga el vehículo de radiocomunicaciones operativo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/taskopt_station"
msgid "Don't let the enemy tanks enter the train station"
msgstr "No permita a los blindados soviéticos entrar en la estación de tren."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1943_02_krasny_bor/timer"
msgid "Prepare for the enemy attack!"
msgstr "Prepárese para el ataque enemigo!"
